<subSubSection id="DCCBBC87FFC300426892FF42FC3E8F13" pageId="40" pageNumber="541" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="946EEF0CFFC300426892FF42FC3E8F13" blockId="40.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis id="A6A5331EFFC300426892FF42FEE78EC7" bold="true" box="[151,274,150,176]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
SIF = SIF = 7BS-N(b)-3-3111.1000; fsp = 7.7.7; fCx = 1.1.1; fSt = 2.2; fPp = B/B/NNB; fSc: PL&gt; AM ≥ AL; Ip = 941–1064; fD = (6–8)H-(6–11)-(7–10)-(7–10)-(6–8)+(4–7); DS = 38–50; V = 34–44; NDV = 72–91. Galeal seta nude or having 1 branch; scutum nearly pentagonal, densely punctated, with rounded, greatly projected posterior margin; AM posterior to level of AL; two PPL setae present on scutal margin posterior to PL; sensilla flagelliform, nude or having few cilia; scutal and dorsal idiosomal setae thick, sparsely covered with small scalelike barbs. Standard measurements of examined specimens given in 
<tableCitation id="D953DAB7FFC300426B66FE9EFC328F13" box="[867,967,330,356]" captionStart="TABLE 14" captionStartId="40.[151,239,404,428]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="TABLE 14. Morphometric (AW–dmt, µm; m-t—ratio) and meristic (DS–NDV) traits of Hoffmannina libita (n = 7)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/C0AEBF84FFC300426892FE40FA9A8FDB" pageId="40" pageNumber="541" tableUuid="C0AEBF84FFC300426892FE40FA9A8FDB">Table 14</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
